HEADWORD: Filoselle
<hw>Fil`o*selle"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., floss
silk.]</ety> <def>A kind of silk thread less glossy than floss, and spun
from coarser material. It is much used in embroidery instead of
floss.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

